[6] studied how several implicit measures related to the interests of the user.
They built an instrumented browser to collect data and then developed Bayesian models to relate implicit measures and explicit relevance judgments for both individual queries and search sessions.
found that the time spent on a page, the amount of scrolling on a page, and the combination of time and scrolling have a strong positive relationship with explicit interest, while individual scrolling methods and mouse-clicks were not correlated with explicit interest.
